<h2>How to Build Your Podcast Stack</h2>
<p>Do not subscribe to all 75. That is a recipe for an overwhelming feed and zero retention. Pick 4 to 6 shows based on your role and goals.</p>
<p><strong>If you are new to SEO:</strong> Start with The SEO Show, Marketing School, and SEO 101. These 3 cover fundamentals, daily updates, and practical tips. Then read our <a href="/blog/seo-for-beginners/">beginner SEO guide</a> alongside what you learn.</p>
<p><strong>If you manage SEO for a business:</strong> Follow SERP's Up, Authority Hacker, and The SEJ Show. Add Search Off the Record for direct Google insight. Pair with our <a href="/blog/seo-checklist-2026/">SEO checklist</a> for implementation.</p>
<p><strong>If you run a local service business:</strong> Local SEO Tactics, Near Memo, and The Recipe for SEO Success cover local-specific strategy. Combine with our <a href="/blog/local-seo-guide/">local SEO guide</a> to put what you hear into action.</p>
<p><strong>If you build content sites:</strong> Authority Hacker, Niche Pursuits, and The Blogging Millionaire teach content-driven growth with real data. Our guide on <a href="/blog/scale-blog-content-ai/">scaling content with AI</a> complements their strategies.</p>
<p><strong>If you work in B2B or SaaS:</strong> Breaking B2B, B2B Growth, and GrowthTLDR cover growth from different angles. See our <a href="/blog/seo-for-b2b/">B2B SEO guide</a> for tactical implementation.</p>
<p><strong>If you want to prepare for AI search:</strong> Marketing AI Podcast, SEO Unlocked, and Voices of Search cover the AI transition. Read our <a href="/blog/generative-engine-optimization-guide/">generative engine optimization guide</a> for the execution side.</p>
